<TITLE> Iraqi Shia leader appears after cancer treatment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BAGHDAD, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Senior Iraqi Shia leader Abdul Aziz al-Hakim made his first public appearance in five months on Saturday after undergoing treatment for lung cancer. Hakim, who has been receiving chemotherapy treatment in Iran, waved to a large, cheering crowd at his southern Baghdad home after Eid al-Fitr prayers to mark the end of the Muslim holy month of Ramadan. Hakim's son Ammar has been running the Supreme Islamic Iraqi Council (SIIC), Iraq's largest Shia political bloc, during his father's illness
